`isEmpty` already checks for nulls so Vasyl's proposal should work. I would also add this:
```
if((pt1Props == pt2Props) || (isEmpty(pt1Props) && isEmpty(pt2Props)))
  return true;
else if (isPropertiesListSizesEquals(pt1Props, pt2Props))
  return false;
else {
  // the rest of the code.
}
```
But overall, there is clearly a design issue that is screaming to be solved here. These "optimizations" seem to be here for performance purpose. What size are the lists passed in argument? If we are not talking about hundreds of elements, I would simplify this logic.
